org.locationtech.geowave.core.store.data

Class IndexedPersistenceEncoding<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.locationtech.geowave.core.store.data.PersistenceEncoding<T>
      • org.locationtech.geowave.core.store.data.IndexedPersistenceEncoding<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CommonIndexedPersistenceEncoding

    public class IndexedPersistenceEncoding<T>
extends PersistenceEncoding<T>
    This class models all of the necessary information for persisting data in the data store (following the common index model) and is used internally within GeoWave as an intermediary object between the direct storage format and the native data format. It also contains information about the persisted object within a particular index such as the insertion ID in the index and the number of duplicates for this entry in the index, and is used when reading data from the index.
